# System Design Document: Regional Electronic Surveillance Platform for Polio and Measles

## Prepared for: Pan American Health Organization 

## Prepared by: HISP Centre at the University of Oslo and HISP Colombia

**Last updated: 15 September 2023**

# Background

At the request of the PAHO Regional Office, the UiO presents this document for review and validation which is a detailed compilation of the information required for the design and development of the new Surveillance system, which will replace the current ISIS system, as a regional platform and eventually, to be available for countries that want to implement it at the national level. 

PAHO's Immunization Program needs to develop strategies for monitoring, control, and elimination of vaccine-preventable diseases in the Latin American region. To do this, it is necessary to have tools that facilitate Member States the process of reporting on progress in this regard as well as allowing PAHO to take different actions, such as providing feedback to countries on data received, preparing periodic bulletins and sharing information with other instances, like WHO. 

The UiO team has been working jointly with the Department of Family, Health Promotion and Life Course Immunization team in the requirements gathering process, which was initiated in October of 2022\.

The solution proposed is aligned with the objectives and scope of assignments indicated in the TORs, that:

* It´s focused but not limited to Measles / Rubella, CRS and Polio  A web-based platform.  This is one of the most relevant characteristics of the solution since other diseases will be able to be included/configure in the future if required  
* It has customizable data entry interface  
* It has interoperable capabilities   
* It has the capacity to access the platform offline or where the internet connection is not good or not available at all. This is feasible using the mobile Android DHIS2 App. It will be demonstrated to the PAHO team when required.  
* It has administration tools   
* It´s administrable and manageable. This will be possible due the Capacity Building activities included in the whole process

## Organisation Unit Hierarchy 

The OU hierarchy follows the structure already in place for PAHO’s regional system (ISIS), which only goes to the Municipality level.

All organisation units have shapefiles (where available); municipalities at L4 also use polygons (no coordinates).

## Organisation Unit Groups

Org unit groups are used to group countries (and their children) in sub-regions, which are often used in regional bulletins or visualizations. Each group contains the respective countries and subdivisions.

* AND  
* CAP  
* LAC  
* NORTH AMERICA  
* MEXICO  
* SOC

## Organisation Unit Group Sets

The OUGS ‘Regions’ is used as a data dimension to slice the data in the analytics tools.

Note that org units within an OUGS \*must\* be exclusive (that is, one OU cannot belong to more than one OUG within the same OUGS)

## User Roles

The VPD-SMART system has 9 types of user roles, each serving different purposes in data capture and management processes. These roles are distributed as follows:

1. **Administrators**  
   * **SuperAdmin:**  
     * **Permissions:**  
       * **Available app authorities:** With this role, users can access any application installed in the DHIS2 system.  
       * **Available tracker authorities:** This role allows users to perform the following actions:  
         * Search Tracked Entity Instance in All Org Units  
         * Ignore validation of required fields in Tracker and Event Capture  
         * Delete enrollment and associated events  
         * View event analytics  
         * Delete tracked entity instance and associated enrollments and events  
         * Administer program dashboard configuration  
         * Tracker importer (experimental)  
         * Merge tracked entity instances  
         * Mark events as incomplete  
       * **Available import/export authorities:** Similarly, users can perform data migration processes with the following actions:  
         * Import events  
         * Export data  
         * Skip data import audit  
         * Import data  
         * Import metadata  
         * Export events  
         * Export metadata  
       * **Available system authorities:** This role also includes full authority to modify metadata, data, and other actions in the system.  
   * **VPD-Admin:**  
     * **Permissions:**  
       * **Available app authorities:** This role grants access to applications such as Tracker, data import/export, and system configurations.  
       * **Available tracker authorities:** This role allows users to perform the following actions:  
         * Merge tracked entity instances  
         * Search Tracked Entity Instance in All Org Units  
         * Delete enrollment and associated events  
         * View event analytics  
         * Manage program rule  
         * Delete tracked entity instance and associated enrollments and events  
         * Administer program dashboard configuration  
       * **Available import/export authorities:** Not applicable.  
       * **Available system authorities:** Not applicable.  
2. **Data Entry Personnel**  
   * **VPD-MR-VIG LIMITED AUTHORITIES (Lab data):** This role is designed for capturing laboratory data in the Final Result, Sequencing, Intratypic Differentiation, and Viral Isolation stages (program rule "IisAMNKD7VW").  
     * **Other features:** Not applicable.  
   * **VPD-MR-LAB LIMITED AUTHORITIES (Lab data):** This role permits data capture only in the Specimen section for fields: Date sent to process, Type of Sample, Date of sample collection, and Sample Number.  
     * **Other features:** Not applicable.  
   * **VPD \- Data entry:**  
     * **Available app authorities:** This role provides access to applications such as Data Entry (Beta), Event Visualizer, Event Reports, Messaging, and Dashboard.  
     * **Available tracker authorities:** Not applicable.  
     * **Available import/export authorities:** Not applicable.  
     * **Available system authorities:** Not applicable.  
   * **VPD \- Data capture:**  
     * **Available app authorities:** This role grants access to applications like Browser Cache Cleaner, Capture, and Dashboard.  
     * **Available tracker authorities:** This role allows users to perform the following actions:  
       * Search Tracked Entity Instance in All Org Units  
       * Merge tracked entity instances  
       * View event analytics  
       * Update tracked entities  
       * Administer program dashboard configuration  
     * **Available import/export authorities:** Not applicable.  
     * **Available system authorities:** Not applicable.  
   * **VPD-AFP-VIG LIMITED AUTHORITIES (Lab data):** With this role, users can only capture data from the Specimen and Type of sample sections.  
     * **Fields:** Specimen, Type of sample, Sample Number, Date of sample collection, Date sent, Laboratory name, Date received, Internal sample code 1\.  
     * **Other features:** Not applicable.  
   * **VPD-AFP-LAB LIMITED AUTHORITIES (Lab data):** This role is specifically for capturing information in sections such as Genotyping (Rubella), Viral Detection (Rubella), Genotyping (Measles), Viral Detection (Measles), and positive tests for other viruses (Rubella and Measles).  
     * **Other features:** Not applicable.  
3. **Data Analysts**  
   * **VPD \- Analytics:** This role is solely for visualizing and generating data reports.  
     * **Other features:** Not applicable.  
     * **Available app authorities:**  
       * Interpretation app  
       * EpiWeek app  
       * Event Reports app  
       * Data Visualizer app  
       * Dashboard app  
       * Information app  
       * Browser Cache Cleaner app  
       * Linelisting app  
       * HMIS Dictionary app  
       * Maps app  
     * **Available tracker authorities:**  
       * View event analytics  
     * **Available import/export authorities:** Not applicable.  
     * **Available system authorities:** Not applicable.

 

## User Groups

The user groups implemented in the VPD system play a crucial role in managing access and modification permissions for metadata based on specific user requirements. Below is a detailed explanation of the functionality of each group:

1. **VPD \- Admins Member:** This group is intended for country-level administrators who need the ability to modify metadata and captured data within the system. It grants them authority over administrative processes without requiring super administrator privileges.

 

2. **VPD \- Dashboards Users:** Users in this group have restricted privileges to review and modify analytical reports derived from collected data. This restriction ensures that only designated users can access and manipulate analytical resources as needed.

 

3. **VPD \- Email Users Alerts:** Key users in this group are selected to receive notifications based on predefined validation rules. These alerts are crucial for cases that require review and follow-up, typically due to specific classifications or unique characteristics.

 

4. **VPD \- Email Users Alerts Prod:** Similar to the previous group, this segment identifies and notifies key users regarding cases that require prompt review and follow-up actions based on predefined rules and criteria.

 

5. **VPD \- English Speaking Users:** This group manages translations related to CORS and other specific needs as requested by the VPD-PAHO team, ensuring seamless communication and understanding among English-speaking users.

 

6. **VPD \- Lab Users:** Access to data capture is restricted to authorized users specifically assigned to laboratory modules. This restriction ensures data integrity by preventing unauthorized modifications in fields outside the designated laboratory context.  
     
7. **VPD \- Measles Users:** Users in this group are restricted to accessing and capturing information exclusively related to the Measles program. This limitation ensures that only designated users can interact with and review data and metadata pertinent to the Measles program.  
      
8. **VPD \- Polio Users:** Structured similarly to the Measles Users group, this segment restricts access and modification permissions to information specifically related to the Polio program, maintaining data integrity and program-focused management.  
      
9. **VPD \- Regional Users:** This group facilitates broader access to metadata, enabling users to conduct comprehensive reviews of analytical data at a regional level. It supports informed decision-making and strategic planning by providing access to detailed analytical insights.  
      
10. **VPD \- Spanish Speaking Users:** Specific translations related to CORS and other identified needs are implemented for this user group based on requirements specified by the VPD-PAHO team. This ensures effective communication and utilization of the system among Spanish-speaking users.

These user groups are meticulously designed to align with organizational roles and operational requirements, ensuring secure and efficient management of data access and manipulation within the VPD system.

 

## Naming conventions

To facilitate filtering and to make it easier for the user to identify what they are analyzing, the following prefixes are used on long names to distinguish between Measles/Rubella (MR) and AFP/Polio (POL):

* MR \- Name  
* POL \- Name

# Tracker Programs 

### Program structure: Polio

* **Programs ( Disease data collection forms)**

  Tracker programs will be created for Measles and Rubella, and another for Polio. This is the type of Program in DHIS2 that provides follow up and to track the entity defined, Cases

  A list of main characteristics by alternatives presented in this document, has been included at the end of this section.  

  * **Program Stages** 

  The stages is a mechanism of the DHIS2 Tracker Program that allows replication within the system, the data capture workflow, in a way, that according to it, one or several stages can be included in a program. . The concept of Program Stage has been included in the Glossary of Terms section in this document.  In a Tracker Program at least one Stage has to be defined.  Using more than one it depends on the workflow and the different steps in this latter and also the users permissions and role in each step. For instance, in the Measles program, it is intended to have

  - **A Registration process,** called Enrolment in DHIS2– to capture all the personal information required by the case.  This is a one-time process and intends to create an enrolment per patient per Program.  This step also applies if using Case as an Entity.  


  Specifically, the stages for each Program identified are listed below.  Take note that those can be adjusted or changed during the configuration process and according to the use cases that can be identified during the testing and validation process.  At this point the stages suggested for the diseases of Polio and Measles/Rubella are:

    * Clinical information: Vaccination History, Trips, Clinical data.  
    * Laboratory: Information about specimens, laboratory tests and results  
    * Final classification.

 Vaccination history and clinical data

![][image3]

* **Data Set \- Aggregates**

  In DHIS2 it is also possible to enter data in a more aggregated level.  This is, instead of case by case, identifying the patient(or case), there is a data entry application, called Data Set, that allows to enter totals, disaggregated by some criterion if necessary, for example:

* Sex  
* Age Range

  For the solution proposed, the following Data sets would be created 

* **The Population data entry,** in order to calculate the rates in the system.  
* **The CRS data entry**  
* **Site notification for negatives**

# Customizations: Scripts & Forms

Script

- Assign EPI week & EPI Year based on the Enrollmment date  
- For Polio: enrollment date is the date of initiation of paralysis  
- For Measles: enrollment date is the date of initiation of rash   
- Therefore, Epi week and Epi year assignment are based on the date of initiation of symptoms in both cases

Custom form 

- Polio Tracker Program: makes the columns show left and right for inputting data on location of paralysis on the body
